<HEADLINE>
FT  30 DEC 94 / BA and Virgin reopen price war
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Airways will today announce its biggest batch of ticket bargains
since its World Offer programme was launched in March, with cut-price fares
available on more than 200 routes.
The move brought an immediate response from Mr Richard Branson's Virgin
Atlantic airline, which said it would undercut BA's prices by Pounds 1 on
all routes which the two airlines both operate.
BA said savings on the usual lowest return fares range from Pounds 10-Pounds
20 on domestic routes to Pounds 454 for flights to Manila.
