<HEADLINE>
FT  30 DEC 94 / Milton Keynes Tec and chamber merge
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Milton Keynes Chamber of Commerce and the Milton Keynes and North
Buckinghamshire Training and Enterprise Council have merged in a move aimed
at streamlining business services and training on a local level.
The move is the first of its kind, though it is understood that at least 10
other chambers and Tecs - the employer-led bodies which administer
government-funded training in England and Wales - are considering similar
partnerships.
The merged body will pool the memberships and provide the central services
that were administered by both individual bodies.
