<TEXT>
AMB, the German insurance group, is planning to raise its stake in
Assurances Generales de France to 5 per cent and become part of a group of
stable shareholders when the French insurer is privatised, writes John
Ridding. The German company, which currently holds 2.57 per cent of AGF,
