   By TIM BURT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Wellcome, the drugs group, yesterday predicted it would win a larger share
of the US market - the world's largest - following approval of two products
by the Food and Drug Administration.
The company welcomed the decision to approve Lamictal, its anti-epilepsy
treatment, and Navelbine, which it claimed would be the first new cancer
drug in the US for 20 years. Both products will be marketed by Burroughs
Wellcome, its US arm.
