   DHAKA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Opposition members of Bangladesh's parliament last night resigned en masse
in an attempt to oust the government of Mrs Khaleda Zia, writes Reazuddin
Ahmed in Dhaka.
The opposition has been boycotting parliamentary sessions for 10 months to
press home their demand for early polls conducted under a non-partisan
caretaker government to allay the fear of election-rigging by the ruling
party.
The ruling Bangladesh Nationalist Party agreed to an opposition proposal
that the prime minister resign 30 days before the next general election, due
in February 1996. But a deal foundered on BNP demands that the opposition
refrain from calling general strikes and blockades during the next year.
