FT  28 DEC 94 / NHS charges
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
About half of all National Health Service prescription items - 222.8m out of
the 445.4m - cost less than the prescription charge, the government
acknowledged in a Commons written answer. Government figures also show that
NHS spending on health services from private-sector providers has risen 70
per cent in two years - from Pounds 208.5m in 1991-92 to a provisional
Pounds 357.4m in 1993-94.
