<HEADLINE>
FT  28 DEC 94 / MP protests over Mercury offer
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Labour MP, Mr Andrew MacKinlay, said yesterday he would protest to Mr
Michael Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, about the fact that
thousands of people who had been 'enticed' into purchasing a Mercury
One-2-One mobile telephone on the promise of unlimited free calls on
Christmas day could not get through.
Mercury One-2-One said at least 20 people had spent more than 12 hours on
the phone on Christmas day. Another 20 had made more than 2,000 calls
between them.
</TEXT>
