<HEADLINE>
FT  28 DEC 94 / Corruption worries Mahathir
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Dr Mahathir Mohamad, Malaysia's prime minister, says he is worried that
corruption recently disclosed in the Malaysian football league might spread
to the country's political system.
Malaysian police have arrested at least 50 football players in recent days
on suspicion of fixing the results of matches. Dr Mahathir said that he was
concerned that if people were willing to offer money to ensure a side wins
in a football match then they might also indulge in similar practices in the
political arena.
The investigations into football bribery in Malaysia comes at a time of
mounting allegations about corruption in various sectors of Malaysian
society.
