<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 94 / World News in Brief: Takeover activity drives London market
up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The driving forces behind the London stock market this week have been the
agreed bid for Portals, the security paper manufacturer, from De La Rue, and
the Trafalgar House bid for Northern Electric, which triggered a wave of
takeover speculation throughout the utilities areas. The FT-SE 100 index
ended the day 8.3 points off at 3,083.4, its first decline in six trading
sessions, but remained 69.8 points, or 2.3 per cent, higher on the week.
Call for probe into Northern Electric's share price, Page 8
London stocks, Page 13
Lex, Page 18
Markets, Weekend Money 2
